j-core: There are test failures.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I ran the test in a debugger.&lt;br/&gt;
The expected value (Constants.LINE_SEP) is &quot;\r\n&quot; on my platform (Windows).&lt;br/&gt;
The actual value (throwableFormatOptions.getSeparator()) is &quot;\n&quot;. (So the pattern &quot;separator(\n)&quot; is parsed correctly.)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The solution would be to either change the expected value to match the pattern or the other way around.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ThrowableFormatOptionsTest.testSeparatorAsDefaultLineSeparator (line 140)&lt;br/&gt;
Current: &lt;br/&gt;
  test(new String[]&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;separator(\n)&quot;}, Integer.MAX_VALUE, Constants.LINE_SEP, null);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Proposed:&lt;br/&gt;
  test(new String[]{&quot;separator(n)&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;, Integer.MAX_VALUE, &quot;\n&quot;, null);&lt;br/&gt;
or:&lt;br/&gt;
  String pattern = &quot;separator(&quot; + Constants.LINE_SEP + &quot;)&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
  test(new String[]&lt;/p&gt;
{pattern}
&lt;p&gt;, Integer.MAX_VALUE, Constants.LINE_SEP, null);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
